WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.859 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.859 --> 00:00:12.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hello and welcome.

00:00:12.150 --> 00:00:12.770 align:middle line:90%
I'm Lisa Garr.

00:00:12.770 --> 00:00:15.210 align:middle line:10%
We are broadcasting from
beautiful downtown Denver,

00:00:15.210 --> 00:00:17.740 align:middle line:10%
Colorado where
Gaiam TV is located.

00:00:17.740 --> 00:00:20.980 align:middle line:84%
So do you ever wonder what it
means to break an old habit,

00:00:20.980 --> 00:00:23.000 align:middle line:84%
or do you wonder why
it's so hard to break?

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:25.550 align:middle line:84%
And do you want to learn how
to be more positive and more

00:00:25.550 --> 00:00:28.080 align:middle line:84%
resilient, but you
just don't know how?

00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:30.550 align:middle line:84%
What if you saw what it
looks like physically

00:00:30.550 --> 00:00:33.540 align:middle line:84%
in the brain for the brain
to be stuck in a pattern.

00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:35.490 align:middle line:84%
Or even better, what
it looks like when

00:00:35.490 --> 00:00:39.210 align:middle line:84%
you break an old habit and
you create a positive change.

00:00:39.210 --> 00:00:40.710 align:middle line:84%
These images we're
going to show you

00:00:40.710 --> 00:00:42.740 align:middle line:90%
later made a huge impact on me.

00:00:42.740 --> 00:00:46.270 align:middle line:84%
What it means to be
literally rewiring the brain.

00:00:46.270 --> 00:00:49.440 align:middle line:84%
Joining me is neuroscientist
and also an expert in brain

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:52.530 align:middle line:84%
function and brain chemistry,
and also one of the scientists

00:00:52.530 --> 00:00:55.291 align:middle line:84%
from the film "What the Bleep
Do We Know!?," Dr. Joe Dispenza.

00:00:55.291 --> 00:00:55.790 align:middle line:90%
Hi.

00:00:55.790 --> 00:00:56.890 align:middle line:90%
>>JOE DISPENZA: Hi Lisa.

00:00:56.890 --> 00:00:58.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great to have you here.

00:00:58.050 --> 00:00:58.750 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Happy
to be with you.

00:00:58.750 --> 00:01:00.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're going to
make some changes today.

00:01:00.250 --> 00:01:00.780 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: I hope.

00:01:00.780 --> 00:01:02.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're going to
break some habits, Joe.

00:01:02.140 --> 00:01:03.980 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Alright,
let's do it.

00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:06.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you have
an enormous amount

00:01:06.850 --> 00:01:10.070 align:middle line:84%
of credibility in this area,
because you did this yourself

00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:11.060 align:middle line:90%
physically.

00:01:11.060 --> 00:01:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And I know that this
happened a while ago,

00:01:13.140 --> 00:01:16.410 align:middle line:84%
but if you could just remind
our listeners how you healed

00:01:16.410 --> 00:01:20.230 align:middle line:84%
your body completely from a
massive spinal cord injury.

00:01:20.230 --> 00:01:23.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, I think
in order for us to wake up,

00:01:23.120 --> 00:01:24.390 align:middle line:90%
we need a wake up call.

00:01:24.390 --> 00:01:27.840 align:middle line:90%
And in 1986, I got the call.

00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:30.141 align:middle line:84%
I was in a triathlon in
Palm Springs, California.

00:01:30.141 --> 00:01:31.765 align:middle line:84%
I was in the biking
portion of the race

00:01:31.765 --> 00:01:34.636 align:middle line:84%
and I was negotiating a
turn, and the police officer

00:01:34.636 --> 00:01:36.135 align:middle line:84%
that was helping
me to make the turn

00:01:36.135 --> 00:01:38.070 align:middle line:84%
had his back to the
oncoming traffic.

00:01:38.070 --> 00:01:41.230 align:middle line:84%
So the moment I made the turn,
this four wheel drive Bronco

00:01:41.230 --> 00:01:44.410 align:middle line:84%
going 55 miles an hour just
clipped me from behind.

00:01:44.410 --> 00:01:47.360 align:middle line:84%
And I landed pretty
squarely on the ground

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:52.030 align:middle line:84%
and ultimately wound up breaking
six vertebrae in my spine.

00:01:52.030 --> 00:01:53.920 align:middle line:10%
Some bone fragments
on the spinal cord,

00:01:53.920 --> 00:02:00.020 align:middle line:10%
and it had created some
neurological problems for me.

00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:01.910 align:middle line:10%
And the conventional
treatment for that

00:02:01.910 --> 00:02:03.780 align:middle line:10%
is a Harrington
rod surgery where

00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:06.355 align:middle line:10%
they cut the back parts
of your vertebrae off

00:02:06.355 --> 00:02:08.925 align:middle line:10%
and then they screw in these
long stainless steel rods.

00:02:08.925 --> 00:02:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's not just
one surgery, that's multiple,

00:02:11.300 --> 00:02:11.550 align:middle line:90%
isn't it?

00:02:11.550 --> 00:02:13.175 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, it
could be multiple.

00:02:13.175 --> 00:02:15.843 align:middle line:84%
But the purpose of
the Harrington rods

00:02:15.843 --> 00:02:18.790 align:middle line:84%
is to pull the spine
back-- the spinal column

00:02:18.790 --> 00:02:20.970 align:middle line:84%
off the spinal cord
to stabilize it.

00:02:20.970 --> 00:02:24.440 align:middle line:84%
And it sounded like a
good idea for any patient

00:02:24.440 --> 00:02:26.980 align:middle line:84%
that I see with that condition,
I would recommend surgery.

00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:30.950 align:middle line:84%
But this was me, and I wasn't
so quick to just rush into it.

00:02:30.950 --> 00:02:34.480 align:middle line:10%
So after four opinions from
four of the leading surgeons

00:02:34.480 --> 00:02:37.150 align:middle line:10%
in Southern California,
I really had

00:02:37.150 --> 00:02:39.680 align:middle line:10%
to make a significant decision.

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:43.360 align:middle line:84%
Do I weigh my old beliefs
against a new paradigm

00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:46.600 align:middle line:84%
and jump off into the unknown
and try something new?

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:49.400 align:middle line:84%
If there's an intelligence
that's giving us life,

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:50.810 align:middle line:90%
could I make contact with it?

00:02:50.810 --> 00:02:54.560 align:middle line:84%
Could I give it a specific
plan, instructions, a template,

00:02:54.560 --> 00:02:56.300 align:middle line:84%
and then surrender
it to a greater mind

00:02:56.300 --> 00:02:58.390 align:middle line:84%
and allow it to do
the healing for me?

00:02:58.390 --> 00:03:00.550 align:middle line:84%
Or do I stick with
the conventional model

00:03:00.550 --> 00:03:05.570 align:middle line:84%
and take the safe route and
possibly have a handicap

00:03:05.570 --> 00:03:07.180 align:middle line:84%
and live on
addictive medications

00:03:07.180 --> 00:03:08.030 align:middle line:90%
the rest of my life?

00:03:08.030 --> 00:03:12.700 align:middle line:84%
So I decided to go from
a philosophical realm

00:03:12.700 --> 00:03:15.430 align:middle line:84%
and to initiate that, to try
to create a new experience.

00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:17.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's so
much science behind how

00:03:17.750 --> 00:03:20.330 align:middle line:84%
the medications and
the surgery works,

00:03:20.330 --> 00:03:23.730 align:middle line:84%
and that has all been documented
and verified and so forth.

00:03:23.730 --> 00:03:26.140 align:middle line:84%
So it would make
sense, and most of us

00:03:26.140 --> 00:03:27.649 align:middle line:90%
make decisions based on that.

00:03:27.649 --> 00:03:28.690 align:middle line:90%
Oh, this has been proven.

00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:29.480 align:middle line:90%
It's been done before.

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:30.355 align:middle line:90%
People have survived.

00:03:30.355 --> 00:03:32.410 align:middle line:84%
They have this kind
of quality of life.

00:03:32.410 --> 00:03:34.022 align:middle line:90%
The other isn't so proven.

00:03:34.022 --> 00:03:34.730 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Yeah.

00:03:34.730 --> 00:03:37.580 align:middle line:84%
You know, I was accused of
having post traumatic stress

00:03:37.580 --> 00:03:39.860 align:middle line:84%
disorder and that I hit
my head and this was not

00:03:39.860 --> 00:03:42.290 align:middle line:84%
a logical decision
for a young guy.

00:03:42.290 --> 00:03:44.520 align:middle line:84%
But I mean really,
upon reflection,

00:03:44.520 --> 00:03:45.690 align:middle line:90%
it's really just two models.

00:03:45.690 --> 00:03:48.210 align:middle line:84%
There's a mechanistic
model of reality

00:03:48.210 --> 00:03:51.330 align:middle line:84%
where when things
break, you fix them.

00:03:51.330 --> 00:03:53.850 align:middle line:84%
But then there's also a
vitalistic model of reality

00:03:53.850 --> 00:03:56.480 align:middle line:90%
that transcends materialism.

00:03:56.480 --> 00:04:00.470 align:middle line:84%
And that vitalistic model
says that there's energy,

00:04:00.470 --> 00:04:03.150 align:middle line:84%
there's information,
there's an intelligence

00:04:03.150 --> 00:04:05.890 align:middle line:84%
that's organizing
trillions of functions

00:04:05.890 --> 00:04:07.770 align:middle line:84%
per second in every
cell of your body.

00:04:07.770 --> 00:04:12.870 align:middle line:84%
And if that intelligence is a
consciousness and an awareness,

00:04:12.870 --> 00:04:15.380 align:middle line:84%
then maybe you can
become present with it

00:04:15.380 --> 00:04:18.089 align:middle line:84%
enough to begin to give
it some instructions.

00:04:18.089 --> 00:04:20.950 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought, hell, I
might as well take a chance.

00:04:20.950 --> 00:04:23.660 align:middle line:84%
I can't heal my back, but a
greater mind can do it for me.

00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:27.790 align:middle line:84%
So I thought if my will matches
its will, if my mind matches

00:04:27.790 --> 00:04:31.260 align:middle line:84%
its mind, and if my love for
life matches its love for life,

00:04:31.260 --> 00:04:32.470 align:middle line:90%
it should answer the call.

00:04:32.470 --> 00:04:34.430 align:middle line:84%
So I wanted to develop
a relationship with it

00:04:34.430 --> 00:04:36.820 align:middle line:84%
and give it really
specific instructions.

00:04:36.820 --> 00:04:39.517 align:middle line:84%
And if I lost my focus or
if I lost my attention,

00:04:39.517 --> 00:04:41.100 align:middle line:84%
I would stop and
start all over again.

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:42.831 align:middle line:84%
And that's really when
I started to learn

00:04:42.831 --> 00:04:44.830 align:middle line:84%
about the mind and the
brain, because I realized

00:04:44.830 --> 00:04:47.260 align:middle line:90%
how unfocused I was, number one.

00:04:47.260 --> 00:04:49.320 align:middle line:84%
And number two, when
we're in crisis or trauma,

00:04:49.320 --> 00:04:51.326 align:middle line:84%
we wind up focusing
on what we don't want

00:04:51.326 --> 00:04:52.450 align:middle line:90%
instead of what we do want.

00:04:52.450 --> 00:04:54.060 align:middle line:84%
So turning that
battleship around

00:04:54.060 --> 00:04:56.169 align:middle line:90%
was my dark night of the soul.

00:04:56.169 --> 00:04:56.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Huge.

00:04:56.710 --> 00:04:57.110 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:04:57.110 --> 00:04:58.390 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: I think
after about six weeks,

00:04:58.390 --> 00:05:00.765 align:middle line:84%
though, I started noticing
some very significant changes.

00:05:00.765 --> 00:05:03.182 align:middle line:84%
That was the moment when I
started noticing those changes,

00:05:03.182 --> 00:05:05.098 align:middle line:84%
that what I was doing
was making a difference.

00:05:05.098 --> 00:05:07.110 align:middle line:84%
And then I started doing
it with more passion.

00:05:07.110 --> 00:05:08.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What was your
specific practice?

00:05:08.990 --> 00:05:12.330 align:middle line:84%
What did you do in those
moments, the small moments?

00:05:12.330 --> 00:05:17.479 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, I
mean I thought this idea

00:05:17.479 --> 00:05:19.520 align:middle line:84%
that the power that made
the body heals the body.

00:05:19.520 --> 00:05:21.260 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I believe
that to this day.

00:05:21.260 --> 00:05:23.930 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that the
quantum model of reality

00:05:23.930 --> 00:05:26.760 align:middle line:84%
explains healing
better than anything.

00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:29.280 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can't
explain how even

00:05:29.280 --> 00:05:31.510 align:middle line:84%
a cut heals without bringing
in the quantum model.

00:05:31.510 --> 00:05:33.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can talk
about molecules,

00:05:33.400 --> 00:05:36.060 align:middle line:84%
and circuits, and chemicals, and
attractions, and propulsion--

00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:36.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And cells
and so forth, yeah--

00:05:36.480 --> 00:05:38.438 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: But that's
really not how it works.

00:05:38.438 --> 00:05:40.360 align:middle line:84%
That's a model
that's very limited.

00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:44.200 align:middle line:84%
So I said if the power that
made the body heals the body,

00:05:44.200 --> 00:05:46.350 align:middle line:84%
and this consciousness
is an awareness,

00:05:46.350 --> 00:05:48.290 align:middle line:84%
and awareness is
paying attention,

00:05:48.290 --> 00:05:50.590 align:middle line:84%
then I have to be
completely present with it.

00:05:50.590 --> 00:05:53.172 align:middle line:84%
Just like when you're with your
daughter and she's with you,

00:05:53.172 --> 00:05:55.630 align:middle line:84%
she knows when you're present
with her and when you're not.

00:05:55.630 --> 00:05:58.420 align:middle line:84%
And you know when she's present
with you and when you're not.

00:05:58.420 --> 00:06:01.110 align:middle line:84%
And this intelligence
requires our presence,

00:06:01.110 --> 00:06:03.290 align:middle line:84%
which means your mind
can't wander to the future

00:06:03.290 --> 00:06:06.130 align:middle line:84%
or to the past and to
extraneous information.

00:06:06.130 --> 00:06:08.460 align:middle line:84%
You have to be
completely present.

00:06:08.460 --> 00:06:13.570 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to create a
very specific instruction.

00:06:13.570 --> 00:06:17.180 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to reconstruct every
single one of my vertebrae step

00:06:17.180 --> 00:06:20.110 align:middle line:84%
by step from start
to stop, and repair

00:06:20.110 --> 00:06:23.800 align:middle line:84%
every single one of those areas
that I knew from the scans.

00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:26.449 align:middle line:84%
And if I lost my focus
because I wasn't present,

00:06:26.449 --> 00:06:28.240 align:middle line:84%
I was thinking about
living in a wheelchair

00:06:28.240 --> 00:06:30.790 align:middle line:84%
or if I should sell my
home or my practice,

00:06:30.790 --> 00:06:31.780 align:middle line:90%
then I lost my focus.

00:06:31.780 --> 00:06:33.450 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't creating
a clear signal.

00:06:33.450 --> 00:06:35.970 align:middle line:84%
I would stop and I would
start all over again.

00:06:35.970 --> 00:06:37.280 align:middle line:90%
Now, here's the problem.

00:06:37.280 --> 00:06:40.350 align:middle line:84%
I would start getting
frustrated that I lost my focus.

00:06:40.350 --> 00:06:42.720 align:middle line:84%
And then when I got
emotional, I got frustrated,

00:06:42.720 --> 00:06:45.380 align:middle line:90%
then I got more unfocused.

00:06:45.380 --> 00:06:48.190 align:middle line:84%
And so after a couple weeks,
I started figuring out

00:06:48.190 --> 00:06:50.760 align:middle line:84%
that instead of reacting,
just to keep bringing it back.

00:06:50.760 --> 00:06:53.060 align:middle line:84%
And I was increasing
my attention span

00:06:53.060 --> 00:06:54.670 align:middle line:90%
during that time.

00:06:54.670 --> 00:06:58.430 align:middle line:84%
And then once I was able to
complete a very clear picture--

00:06:58.430 --> 00:07:00.850 align:middle line:84%
it would take me two or
three, sometimes longer,

00:07:00.850 --> 00:07:03.040 align:middle line:84%
just three hours immersed
in the inner world--

00:07:03.040 --> 00:07:05.770 align:middle line:84%
but I was firing and
wiring new circuits

00:07:05.770 --> 00:07:07.040 align:middle line:90%
over time, every single day.

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:08.290 align:middle line:90%
And it started getting easier.

00:07:08.290 --> 00:07:10.690 align:middle line:84%
Because as nerve cells fire
together, wire together,

00:07:10.690 --> 00:07:13.110 align:middle line:84%
you start constructing
physical changes in the brain.

00:07:13.110 --> 00:07:16.520 align:middle line:84%
Those changes then you can
reactivate the next day,

00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:18.090 align:middle line:84%
and they should be
easier to select.

00:07:18.090 --> 00:07:21.050 align:middle line:84%
So it started getting
easier for me and I started

00:07:21.050 --> 00:07:23.474 align:middle line:84%
to be able to do it in shorter
and shorter amount of time.

00:07:23.474 --> 00:07:25.890 align:middle line:84%
And when I really got through
it the first time from start

00:07:25.890 --> 00:07:28.240 align:middle line:84%
to finish without
losing my focus,

00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:30.400 align:middle line:84%
it was like I hit a tennis
ball in the sweet spot.

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:31.180 align:middle line:90%
Something clicked.

00:07:31.180 --> 00:07:34.090 align:middle line:84%
You know, and when I knew that,
I knew that something happened.

00:07:34.090 --> 00:07:36.590 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I started
feeling all the changes

00:07:36.590 --> 00:07:39.150 align:middle line:84%
in my body, my pain, all
the sensations changing.

00:07:39.150 --> 00:07:42.610 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I knew that
if I was making those changes

00:07:42.610 --> 00:07:44.840 align:middle line:84%
outside of me, I
should pay attention

00:07:44.840 --> 00:07:47.860 align:middle line:84%
to what I was doing inside of me
and do it with more conviction,

00:07:47.860 --> 00:07:48.730 align:middle line:90%
with more intensity.

00:07:48.730 --> 00:07:51.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we're going to see
a video here of cells wiring

00:07:51.190 --> 00:07:52.940 align:middle line:84%
and firing together,
but I want to ask you

00:07:52.940 --> 00:07:54.650 align:middle line:90%
about the quantum model of this.

00:07:54.650 --> 00:07:57.550 align:middle line:84%
So when we see these
neurons that are literally

00:07:57.550 --> 00:08:00.610 align:middle line:84%
creating these bridges,
where is the quantum field

00:08:00.610 --> 00:08:01.502 align:middle line:90%
within the neurons?

00:08:01.502 --> 00:08:02.960 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
the quantum field

00:08:02.960 --> 00:08:06.780 align:middle line:84%
is the space between the
atoms inside the neurons,

00:08:06.780 --> 00:08:10.070 align:middle line:84%
and at the same time, the field
energetically around them.

00:08:10.070 --> 00:08:13.790 align:middle line:84%
So learning is making
new synaptic connections.

00:08:13.790 --> 00:08:15.290 align:middle line:84%
Every time you
learn something new,

00:08:15.290 --> 00:08:17.910 align:middle line:84%
there is a physical change
that takes place in your brain.

00:08:17.910 --> 00:08:20.200 align:middle line:90%
The brain upscales its hardware.

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:22.977 align:middle line:84%
So if you learn
something in this show

00:08:22.977 --> 00:08:24.560 align:middle line:84%
or you learn something
reading a book,

00:08:24.560 --> 00:08:26.320 align:middle line:84%
and you learn something
on a documentary,

00:08:26.320 --> 00:08:29.440 align:middle line:84%
you have a footprint
of consciousness

00:08:29.440 --> 00:08:30.350 align:middle line:90%
left in your brain.

00:08:30.350 --> 00:08:33.970 align:middle line:84%
So consciousness, then, has
to leave material evidence

00:08:33.970 --> 00:08:36.211 align:middle line:84%
of what we've
learned biologically.

00:08:36.211 --> 00:08:38.460 align:middle line:84%
And so if learning is making
new synaptic connections,

00:08:38.460 --> 00:08:40.710 align:middle line:84%
then remembering is maintaining
and sustaining them.

00:08:40.710 --> 00:08:45.890 align:middle line:84%
So how do two neurons know
how to reach across a bridge

00:08:45.890 --> 00:08:47.420 align:middle line:90%
and connect?

