using that emotion
as inspiration.

00:29:30.300 --> 00:29:33.800 align:middle line:84%
They're transmuting the
anger into inspiration

00:29:33.800 --> 00:29:36.030 align:middle line:84%
as long as they
understand its energy.

00:29:36.030 --> 00:29:39.890 align:middle line:84%
Now, if they get in
similar situations that

00:29:39.890 --> 00:29:44.250 align:middle line:84%
create the same emotion because
it's similar to the event that

00:29:44.250 --> 00:29:47.530 align:middle line:84%
happened in the past,
then their challenge

00:29:47.530 --> 00:29:49.770 align:middle line:90%
is to not experience anger.

00:29:49.770 --> 00:29:52.630 align:middle line:84%
Because if they haven't
overcome that anger,

00:29:52.630 --> 00:29:54.090 align:middle line:90%
then they haven't evolved.

00:29:54.090 --> 00:29:55.589 align:middle line:84%
Really what they're
doing is they're

00:29:55.589 --> 00:29:58.990 align:middle line:84%
saying I'm standing up for
the justice of this cause

00:29:58.990 --> 00:30:00.960 align:middle line:84%
because I've been
branded emotionally.

00:30:00.960 --> 00:30:03.350 align:middle line:84%
But they haven't gotten
beyond that emotion yet,

00:30:03.350 --> 00:30:04.990 align:middle line:84%
and it keeps them
anchored to the past.

00:30:04.990 --> 00:30:05.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:30:05.450 --> 00:30:06.866 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes
that's the emotion--

00:30:06.866 --> 00:30:11.770 align:middle line:84%
like an activist that
feeds into that injustice

00:30:11.770 --> 00:30:13.970 align:middle line:84%
in order to propel
them towards justice.

00:30:13.970 --> 00:30:16.210 align:middle line:84%
But you're saying that
it's like the activists

00:30:16.210 --> 00:30:17.610 align:middle line:90%
without the anger.

00:30:17.610 --> 00:30:20.037 align:middle line:84%
And that's how you actually
rewire the brain to create--

00:30:20.037 --> 00:30:20.870 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Exactly.

00:30:20.870 --> 00:30:24.560 align:middle line:84%
So then as you begin to
overcome the emotions

00:30:24.560 --> 00:30:28.100 align:middle line:84%
from past experiences, the
memory without the emotion

00:30:28.100 --> 00:30:29.440 align:middle line:90%
is called wisdom.

00:30:29.440 --> 00:30:32.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's the name of
the game here, isn't it?

00:30:32.290 --> 00:30:33.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's evolving.

00:30:33.490 --> 00:30:34.580 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it's evolving.

00:30:34.580 --> 00:30:38.030 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So then as you begin
to inhibit certain thoughts,

00:30:38.030 --> 00:30:41.535 align:middle line:84%
as you begin to restrain
certain habits, and behaviors,

00:30:41.535 --> 00:30:44.130 align:middle line:84%
and actions, and
choices, and as you

00:30:44.130 --> 00:30:47.800 align:middle line:84%
begin to become aware of the
emotions that keep bringing you

00:30:47.800 --> 00:30:50.890 align:middle line:84%
to a lower denominator, nerve
cells that no longer fire

00:30:50.890 --> 00:30:52.430 align:middle line:84%
together no longer
wire together.

00:30:52.430 --> 00:30:54.320 align:middle line:84%
You begin to
silence the circuits

00:30:54.320 --> 00:30:57.110 align:middle line:84%
in your brain that are
connected to the old self

00:30:57.110 --> 00:30:58.840 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't
use it, you lose it.

00:30:58.840 --> 00:31:01.150 align:middle line:10%
So then there are
physical changes

00:31:01.150 --> 00:31:02.400 align:middle line:10%
that take place in the brain.

00:31:02.400 --> 00:31:04.100 align:middle line:10%
And we call that pruning.

00:31:04.100 --> 00:31:08.540 align:middle line:10%
And so as you begin to no
longer use those circuits,

00:31:08.540 --> 00:31:10.090 align:middle line:10%
the brain doesn't need them.

00:31:10.090 --> 00:31:13.270 align:middle line:84%
So it begins to prune
those connections away.

00:31:13.270 --> 00:31:16.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, every place where
one neuron connects

00:31:16.050 --> 00:31:18.200 align:middle line:84%
with another neuron
is called a memory.

00:31:18.200 --> 00:31:20.280 align:middle line:84%
So if you're pruning
the circuits away

00:31:20.280 --> 00:31:22.260 align:middle line:84%
that are connected
to the old self,

00:31:22.260 --> 00:31:26.770 align:middle line:84%
then the memory of the old self
no longer exists biologically.

00:31:26.770 --> 00:31:28.730 align:middle line:84%
Now, we could say
you're born again

00:31:28.730 --> 00:31:31.130 align:middle line:84%
or we could say
you're reinvented.

00:31:31.130 --> 00:31:33.090 align:middle line:84%
And so then where is
that memory stored?

00:31:33.090 --> 00:31:35.540 align:middle line:84%
And it's stored in
the soul as wisdom.

00:31:35.540 --> 00:31:37.390 align:middle line:84%
And that's when we
get to then begin

00:31:37.390 --> 00:31:39.710 align:middle line:84%
to create new experiences,
because the soul now

00:31:39.710 --> 00:31:42.020 align:middle line:84%
is no longer anchored
to the emotion that

00:31:42.020 --> 00:31:44.077 align:middle line:84%
keeps reliving the
past experience.

00:31:44.077 --> 00:31:45.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So what about you?

00:31:45.160 --> 00:31:46.100 align:middle line:90%
Do you get angry?

00:31:46.100 --> 00:31:46.920 align:middle line:90%
Do you get hooked?

00:31:46.920 --> 00:31:48.000 align:middle line:90%
Do you get tricked?

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:48.290 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: I do.

00:31:48.290 --> 00:31:48.790 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:31:48.790 --> 00:31:50.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we always joke
around about this.

00:31:50.780 --> 00:31:53.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think emotions
are part of life.

00:31:53.310 --> 00:31:56.280 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact,
emotions make life fun.

00:31:56.280 --> 00:31:57.870 align:middle line:84%
And when I react
to something, it's

00:31:57.870 --> 00:31:59.680 align:middle line:84%
not the question
of that I reacted.

00:31:59.680 --> 00:32:02.660 align:middle line:84%
The question is
how long I react.

00:32:02.660 --> 00:32:03.250 align:middle line:90%
Like a kid.

00:32:03.250 --> 00:32:05.650 align:middle line:84%
You see a kid go, I don't
want to put my shoes on.

00:32:05.650 --> 00:32:06.250 align:middle line:90%
You're putting them on.

00:32:06.250 --> 00:32:06.540 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:32:06.540 --> 00:32:07.796 align:middle line:84%
They put their shoes on
and then all right, I've

00:32:07.796 --> 00:32:08.830 align:middle line:90%
got my shoes on.

00:32:08.830 --> 00:32:11.164 align:middle line:84%
So like adults, I mean what's
one of the greatest things

00:32:11.164 --> 00:32:12.455 align:middle line:90%
that we can teach our children?

00:32:12.455 --> 00:32:14.100 align:middle line:84%
Emotional intelligence
is shortening

00:32:14.100 --> 00:32:16.225 align:middle line:84%
the refractory period of
their emotional reactions.

00:32:16.225 --> 00:32:17.002 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:32:17.002 --> 00:32:17.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's resilience.

00:32:17.490 --> 00:32:18.740 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: That's resilience.

00:32:18.740 --> 00:32:21.020 align:middle line:84%
So then if they can't get
beyond their emotions,

00:32:21.020 --> 00:32:22.650 align:middle line:84%
it's going to become
part of their personality

00:32:22.650 --> 00:32:25.233 align:middle line:84%
and they're going to use those
emotions to get what they want.

00:32:25.233 --> 00:32:30.089 align:middle line:84%
So it's key because,
as we live our life,

00:32:30.089 --> 00:32:31.630 align:middle line:84%
we're always going
to be dissatisfied

00:32:31.630 --> 00:32:33.820 align:middle line:84%
or we're going to have thwarted
intentions or unfulfilled

00:32:33.820 --> 00:32:34.095 align:middle line:90%
expectations.

00:32:34.095 --> 00:32:35.678 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot
that's going to go on.

00:32:35.678 --> 00:32:39.270 align:middle line:84%
And you can go damn, ah, and
then just get on with it.

00:32:39.270 --> 00:32:40.020 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that's me.

00:32:40.020 --> 00:32:43.199 align:middle line:84%
I always go-- and my assistant
and I always laugh about it

00:32:43.199 --> 00:32:43.740 align:middle line:90%
all the time.

00:32:43.740 --> 00:32:47.452 align:middle line:84%
Because I always say
don't respond yet.

00:32:47.452 --> 00:32:49.160 align:middle line:84%
Let's wait for the
chemicals to wear off.

00:32:49.160 --> 00:32:50.530 align:middle line:90%
Let's just wait.

00:32:50.530 --> 00:32:51.172 align:middle line:90%
Just wait.

00:32:51.172 --> 00:32:52.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What a great way to--

00:32:52.380 --> 00:32:53.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I know, I want to, too.

00:32:53.780 --> 00:32:55.230 align:middle line:90%
It feels so good.

00:32:55.230 --> 00:32:58.720 align:middle line:84%
But if we get beyond it, then
the gap between the way things

00:32:58.720 --> 00:33:00.990 align:middle line:84%
appear and the way things
really are close down,

00:33:00.990 --> 00:33:03.370 align:middle line:84%
because now we're not
looking at that experience

00:33:03.370 --> 00:33:05.690 align:middle line:90%
through that emotional window.

00:33:05.690 --> 00:33:08.520 align:middle line:84%
So then when the emotion wears
off, you have more clarity,

00:33:08.520 --> 00:33:11.970 align:middle line:84%
you have more resilience,
you can make better choices,

00:33:11.970 --> 00:33:14.050 align:middle line:84%
because that refractory
period has been altered.

00:33:14.050 --> 00:33:16.555 align:middle line:84%
So I don't think
it's bad to react.

00:33:16.555 --> 00:33:18.180 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I came from
an Italian family--

00:33:18.180 --> 00:33:18.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's normal.

00:33:18.590 --> 00:33:20.048 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --it's
just what we do.

00:33:20.048 --> 00:33:22.110 align:middle line:84%
But how long you
react is the question.

00:33:22.110 --> 00:33:26.582 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's
true, true evolution.

00:33:26.582 --> 00:33:28.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's interesting,
because that Italian part

00:33:28.790 --> 00:33:30.580 align:middle line:90%
of you, though, is hardwired.

00:33:30.580 --> 00:33:32.099 align:middle line:84%
And you can and you
have changed it.

00:33:32.099 --> 00:33:33.140 align:middle line:90%
You have evolved out of--

00:33:33.140 --> 00:33:33.810 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Oh,
I certainly have.

00:33:33.810 --> 00:33:34.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --certain areas of that.

