00:33:45.200 --> 00:33:48.200 align:middle line:10%
I want to take a moment and
introduce you to my new book.

00:33:48.200 --> 00:33:50.860 align:middle line:10%
It's called "Breaking the
Habit of Being Yourself:

00:33:50.860 --> 00:33:53.940 align:middle line:10%
How to Lose Your Mind
and Create a New One."

00:33:53.940 --> 00:33:56.000 align:middle line:10%
Now, there's a basic
premise in the book that

00:33:56.000 --> 00:34:00.550 align:middle line:10%
says your personality creates
your personal reality.

00:34:00.550 --> 00:34:04.380 align:middle line:10%
Now, your personality is made up
of how you think, how you act,

00:34:04.380 --> 00:34:06.180 align:middle line:10%
and how you feel.

00:34:06.180 --> 00:34:10.000 align:middle line:84%
So the present personality
who's listening to me right now

00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:14.850 align:middle line:84%
has created the present personal
reality called your life.

00:34:14.850 --> 00:34:16.389 align:middle line:84%
It also means,
then, if you wanted

00:34:16.389 --> 00:34:20.070 align:middle line:84%
to create a new personal
reality, a new life,

00:34:20.070 --> 00:34:21.710 align:middle line:84%
then on a fundamental
level, you would

00:34:21.710 --> 00:34:24.750 align:middle line:84%
have to change some thoughts
that you have about yourself

00:34:24.750 --> 00:34:28.239 align:middle line:84%
or your life,
behaviors or habits

00:34:28.239 --> 00:34:30.370 align:middle line:84%
that you continuously
demonstrate,

00:34:30.370 --> 00:34:33.040 align:middle line:84%
or feelings and
emotional reactions

00:34:33.040 --> 00:34:36.920 align:middle line:84%
that you've memorized that's
become part of your identity.

00:34:36.920 --> 00:34:40.800 align:middle line:84%
Now, the new science
tells us that we are not

00:34:40.800 --> 00:34:43.719 align:middle line:84%
doomed by our genes,
that we're not hard

00:34:43.719 --> 00:34:46.409 align:middle line:84%
wired to be the same for
the rest of our life,

00:34:46.409 --> 00:34:49.520 align:middle line:84%
that we're marvels of
adaptability and change.

00:34:49.520 --> 00:34:52.090 align:middle line:84%
And most people, then--
I think all of us--

00:34:52.090 --> 00:34:54.639 align:middle line:84%
try to create a new
personal reality

00:34:54.639 --> 00:34:56.750 align:middle line:90%
as the same personality.

00:34:56.750 --> 00:34:59.680 align:middle line:84%
But this new science
tells us that we

00:34:59.680 --> 00:35:03.000 align:middle line:84%
can change both our
mind and our bodies

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:07.360 align:middle line:84%
because of this new science
called neuroplasticity.

00:35:07.360 --> 00:35:09.090 align:middle line:84%
Neuroplasticity
tells us that we're

00:35:09.090 --> 00:35:11.400 align:middle line:84%
changed by every
thought we think,

00:35:11.400 --> 00:35:15.540 align:middle line:84%
every experience we have,
every new choice we make,

00:35:15.540 --> 00:35:19.270 align:middle line:84%
every new experience and
emotion that we can conjure up.

00:35:19.270 --> 00:35:23.400 align:middle line:84%
The brain literally changes
to reflect the new mind.

00:35:23.400 --> 00:35:26.200 align:middle line:84%
And because of the
science of epigenetics,

00:35:26.200 --> 00:35:29.820 align:middle line:84%
we can signal new
genes in new ways.

00:35:29.820 --> 00:35:32.570 align:middle line:84%
But if we keep doing
the same things

00:35:32.570 --> 00:35:35.400 align:middle line:84%
and thinking the same
thoughts, and responding

00:35:35.400 --> 00:35:38.030 align:middle line:84%
to the same circumstances
in the same way,

00:35:38.030 --> 00:35:40.810 align:middle line:84%
we keep signaling the
same genes that ultimately

00:35:40.810 --> 00:35:43.860 align:middle line:84%
cause us to head to
our genetic destiny.

00:35:43.860 --> 00:35:45.700 align:middle line:10%
Change your mind,
though, and you

00:35:45.700 --> 00:35:49.510 align:middle line:10%
can begin to signal new genes
that can change your health.

00:35:49.510 --> 00:35:52.140 align:middle line:10%
And because of this
theory in quantum physics

00:35:52.140 --> 00:35:55.710 align:middle line:10%
that says that your
subjective mind

00:35:55.710 --> 00:35:58.490 align:middle line:10%
has an effect on
your objective world,

00:35:58.490 --> 00:36:01.520 align:middle line:10%
then maybe then when we
change how we think and feel

00:36:01.520 --> 00:36:04.900 align:middle line:10%
inside of us, that those
thoughts and feelings become

00:36:04.900 --> 00:36:07.570 align:middle line:10%
the very blueprints
of our destiny.

00:36:07.570 --> 00:36:09.260 align:middle line:90%
This is what the book is about.

00:36:09.260 --> 00:36:11.740 align:middle line:84%
And it gives people
permission to experiment,

00:36:11.740 --> 00:36:14.260 align:middle line:84%
because this is the
time in history where

00:36:14.260 --> 00:36:17.810 align:middle line:84%
people not only want to know,
but they want to know how.

00:36:17.810 --> 00:36:20.010 align:middle line:84%
So after I appeared in
the movie, "What the Bleep

00:36:20.010 --> 00:36:23.320 align:middle line:84%
Do We Know?," when I wrote my
other book called "Evolve Your

00:36:23.320 --> 00:36:25.420 align:middle line:84%
Brain: The Science of
Changing Your Mind,"

00:36:25.420 --> 00:36:28.790 align:middle line:84%
