00:38:43.790 --> 00:38:45.456 align:middle line:84%
why is it you can
give someone the sugar

00:38:45.456 --> 00:38:51.850 align:middle line:84%
pill, a saline injection, or do
a sham surgery, a fake surgery,

00:38:51.850 --> 00:38:55.370 align:middle line:84%
and a certain percentage
of those people get well.

00:38:55.370 --> 00:38:58.480 align:middle line:84%
In other words, they
accept, believe,

00:38:58.480 --> 00:39:01.880 align:middle line:84%
and surrender to the
idea, the thought,

00:39:01.880 --> 00:39:04.680 align:middle line:84%
that that drug that's not a
drug-- it's a sugar pill--

00:39:04.680 --> 00:39:08.660 align:middle line:84%
that saline injection
or that sham surgery,

00:39:08.660 --> 00:39:09.994 align:middle line:90%
is going to produce the effect--

00:39:09.994 --> 00:39:11.285 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What is the percentage?

00:39:11.285 --> 00:39:12.270 align:middle line:90%
Sorry for interrupting.

00:39:12.270 --> 00:39:14.590 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: The percentage,
by the way, in placebos,

00:39:14.590 --> 00:39:18.710 align:middle line:90%
varies from 10% to 100%.

00:39:18.710 --> 00:39:19.380 align:middle line:90%
For example--

00:39:19.380 --> 00:39:19.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:39:19.690 --> 00:39:20.020 align:middle line:90%
It's a wide range.

00:39:20.020 --> 00:39:21.603 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --three
out of four people

00:39:21.603 --> 00:39:25.522 align:middle line:84%
who are given a sugar pill and
told it's an antidepressant,

00:39:25.522 --> 00:39:26.980 align:middle line:84%
three out of those
four people will

00:39:26.980 --> 00:39:29.270 align:middle line:84%
have pretty significant
changes in their depression.

00:39:29.270 --> 00:39:29.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's high.

00:39:29.800 --> 00:39:30.860 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Some
of those people you

00:39:30.860 --> 00:39:32.359 align:middle line:84%
can do a brain scan
on them, and you

00:39:32.359 --> 00:39:36.190 align:middle line:84%
can see that there's been
physical changes in their brain

00:39:36.190 --> 00:39:37.550 align:middle line:90%
as if they've taken the drug.

00:39:37.550 --> 00:39:41.770 align:middle line:84%
In other words, when a
person accepts, believes,

00:39:41.770 --> 00:39:43.950 align:middle line:84%
and surrenders to the
thought that they're

00:39:43.950 --> 00:39:47.070 align:middle line:84%
going to get better
and doesn't analyze it,

00:39:47.070 --> 00:39:50.790 align:middle line:84%
it begins to activate their
autonomic nervous system.

00:39:50.790 --> 00:39:56.100 align:middle line:84%
And now the body makes
its own pharmaceuticals

00:39:56.100 --> 00:39:59.020 align:middle line:84%
to match the exact drug
that they're taking.

00:39:59.020 --> 00:40:02.690 align:middle line:84%
Now, most people, I don't think
they get this on a deep level.

00:40:02.690 --> 00:40:06.790 align:middle line:84%
Because if you begin to
understand that this occurs,

00:40:06.790 --> 00:40:10.370 align:middle line:84%
then I ask the question why
give a person a sugar pill?

00:40:10.370 --> 00:40:12.750 align:middle line:84%
A saline injection
or a sham surgery?

00:40:12.750 --> 00:40:15.307 align:middle line:84%
Why don't we teach them how
to do it by thought alone?

00:40:15.307 --> 00:40:15.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:40:15.890 --> 00:40:18.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And so the
research that we've

00:40:18.500 --> 00:40:21.380 align:middle line:84%
been doing over the last
year and a half or so shows

00:40:21.380 --> 00:40:23.780 align:middle line:84%
that you don't need a sugar
pill or a saline injection

00:40:23.780 --> 00:40:25.020 align:middle line:90%
or a fake surgery.

00:40:25.020 --> 00:40:28.000 align:middle line:84%
That there are three
principles that

00:40:28.000 --> 00:40:29.890 align:middle line:84%
come into the effect
of the placebo.

00:40:29.890 --> 00:40:32.740 align:middle line:84%
And if you can teach people
these three principles,

00:40:32.740 --> 00:40:35.360 align:middle line:84%
you should be able to
produce the same change

00:40:35.360 --> 00:40:36.360 align:middle line:90%
in their state of being.

00:40:36.360 --> 00:40:39.650 align:middle line:10%
So the first principle
is called conditioning.

00:40:39.650 --> 00:40:42.040 align:middle line:10%
And conditioning is
based on the idea

00:40:42.040 --> 00:40:45.680 align:middle line:10%
that if you give someone--
this is a great study.

00:40:45.680 --> 00:40:50.660 align:middle line:10%
They gave a group of children
an inhaler for asthma.

00:40:50.660 --> 00:40:55.470 align:middle line:84%
And what they did was they
blended the scent of cinnamon

00:40:55.470 --> 00:40:59.200 align:middle line:84%
with the stimulation
of the drug.

00:40:59.200 --> 00:41:01.210 align:middle line:84%
And every time they had
an asthmatic reaction,

00:41:01.210 --> 00:41:03.870 align:middle line:84%
they would inhale
the albuterol and it

00:41:03.870 --> 00:41:06.000 align:middle line:90%
would cause bronchial dilation.

00:41:06.000 --> 00:41:08.420 align:middle line:84%
And it would help
them breathe better.

00:41:08.420 --> 00:41:11.350 align:middle line:84%
But what they were doing
is they were inhaling also

00:41:11.350 --> 00:41:15.260 align:middle line:84%
the scent of cinnamon,
unbeknownst to the children.

00:41:15.260 --> 00:41:18.350 align:middle line:84%
And they kept lowering
the value of the drug.

00:41:18.350 --> 00:41:23.740 align:middle line:84%
And the children were just
spraying the cinnamon water

00:41:23.740 --> 00:41:25.130 align:middle line:90%
in their mouth.

00:41:25.130 --> 00:41:30.980 align:middle line:84%
And they were conditioning
their body chemically

00:41:30.980 --> 00:41:34.640 align:middle line:84%
by removing the drug
and anticipating

00:41:34.640 --> 00:41:36.730 align:middle line:90%
the effect of the drug.

00:41:36.730 --> 00:41:39.770 align:middle line:84%
And so it works
with pain as well.

00:41:39.770 --> 00:41:43.216 align:middle line:84%
You can give people
a morphine injection,

00:41:43.216 --> 00:41:45.840 align:middle line:84%
give them a morphine injection,
give them a morphine injection,

00:41:45.840 --> 00:41:47.440 align:middle line:84%
and then don't give them
the morphine injection.

00:41:47.440 --> 00:41:49.160 align:middle line:84%
And the brain makes
their own morphine.

00:41:49.160 --> 00:41:49.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:41:49.660 --> 00:41:52.140 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: You can give
a Parkinson's patient

00:41:52.140 --> 00:41:55.222 align:middle line:84%
a certain drug to help
their dopamine levels.

00:41:55.222 --> 00:41:57.180 align:middle line:84%
Do it again, do it again,
do it again, and then

00:41:57.180 --> 00:41:58.840 align:middle line:90%
give them a saline injection.

00:41:58.840 --> 00:42:01.256 align:middle line:84%
And before you know it, they're
making their own dopamine.

00:42:01.256 --> 00:42:04.780 align:middle line:84%
Now, not just a little
dopamine, 200 times the amount

00:42:04.780 --> 00:42:05.880 align:middle line:90%
of dopamine.

00:42:05.880 --> 00:42:07.840 align:middle line:84%
So if you are
conditioning yourself

00:42:07.840 --> 00:42:09.750 align:middle line:84%
to take an aspirin every
day because it helps

00:42:09.750 --> 00:42:12.640 align:middle line:84%
to reduce your headaches
or your pain in your back,

00:42:12.640 --> 00:42:15.860 align:middle line:84%
in time, then, if you produce a
pill that looks like an aspirin

00:42:15.860 --> 00:42:18.955 align:middle line:84%
and you give it to a patient,
a certain percentage of them

00:42:18.955 --> 00:42:20.670 align:middle line:84%
will accept, believe,
and surrender

00:42:20.670 --> 00:42:23.020 align:middle line:84%
that they're taking the
aspirin when they're just

00:42:23.020 --> 00:42:24.190 align:middle line:90%
taking a saline injection.

00:42:24.190 --> 00:42:27.280 align:middle line:84%
And their body will create
their own anti-inflammatories

00:42:27.280 --> 00:42:28.520 align:middle line:90%
by thought alone.

00:42:28.520 --> 00:42:31.970 align:middle line:84%
Now, they can't consciously
make their pain go away.

00:42:31.970 --> 00:42:35.839 align:middle line:84%
They can't consciously increase
their dopamine levels--

00:42:35.839 --> 00:42:36.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's the routine.

00:42:36.880 --> 00:42:38.338 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --it's
the conditioning

00:42:38.338 --> 00:42:39.960 align:middle line:84%
in which if you
keep conditioning

00:42:39.960 --> 00:42:42.780 align:middle line:84%
the body, the body,
in anticipation,

00:42:42.780 --> 00:42:46.210 align:middle line:84%
just like Pavlov's
dogs, begins to salivate

00:42:46.210 --> 00:42:47.990 align:middle line:90%
when the bell is rang.

00:42:47.990 --> 00:42:50.360 align:middle line:84%
The body begins
to prepare itself

00:42:50.360 --> 00:42:52.890 align:middle line:84%
for the event ahead
of the actual event

00:42:52.890 --> 00:42:56.080 align:middle line:84%
by creating the exact
chemistry in anticipation

00:42:56.080 --> 00:42:57.240 align:middle line:90%
of it occurring.

00:42:57.240 --> 00:43:02.140 align:middle line:84%
So then there's a
great study where

00:43:02.140 --> 00:43:04.110 align:middle line:84%
we talk about
anticipatory nausea.

00:43:04.110 --> 00:43:06.870 align:middle line:84%
Like many, many
people when they're

00:43:06.870 --> 00:43:09.600 align:middle line:84%
going to their first
chemotherapy treatment,

00:43:09.600 --> 00:43:13.300 align:middle line:84%
they get nauseous on their
drive to the first chemotherapy

00:43:13.300 --> 00:43:15.720 align:middle line:84%
treatment because
their doctor told them

00:43:15.720 --> 00:43:18.670 align:middle line:84%
that they were going to
get sick from chemotherapy.

00:43:18.670 --> 00:43:24.160 align:middle line:84%
So on their way
to the treatment,

00:43:24.160 --> 00:43:28.500 align:middle line:84%
they're thinking
about getting nauseous

00:43:28.500 --> 00:43:32.630 align:middle line:84%
and they're accepting
the idea that they could.

00:43:32.630 --> 00:43:35.130 align:middle line:84%
And then in a matter
of moments, they begin,

00:43:35.130 --> 00:43:39.130 align:middle line:84%
their body begins to create the
chemistry to match the thought.

00:43:39.130 --> 00:43:40.820 align:middle line:90%
And they begin to get nauseous.

00:43:40.820 --> 00:43:43.100 align:middle line:84%
So the question is,
if 50% of those people

00:43:43.100 --> 00:43:46.620 align:middle line:84%
can get nauseous on their drive
to their first chemotherapy

00:43:46.620 --> 00:43:48.870 align:middle line:84%
treatment, 50% of the
people in the world

00:43:48.870 --> 00:43:50.690 align:middle line:84%
can get healthy on
their drive to work

00:43:50.690 --> 00:43:52.910 align:middle line:90%
in anticipation of being well.

00:43:52.910 --> 00:43:57.779 align:middle line:84%
We tell our staff at our
clinic, if 50% of those people

00:43:57.779 --> 00:44:00.070 align:middle line:84%
can get sick on their drive
to their first chemotherapy

00:44:00.070 --> 00:44:02.620 align:middle line:84%
treatment, 50% of our patients
can get well on their drive--

00:44:02.620 --> 00:44:04.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because
you're anticipating.

00:44:04.120 --> 00:44:05.495 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --and
because as they

00:44:05.495 --> 00:44:10.900 align:middle line:84%
begin to think about what
the treatment's going to do,

00:44:10.900 --> 00:44:13.980 align:middle line:84%
they begin to make their
own chemicals to match it.

00:44:13.980 --> 00:44:16.070 align:middle line:84%
So which brings me
to the second point,

00:44:16.070 --> 00:44:18.210 align:middle line:84%
which is what we
call expectation.

00:44:18.210 --> 00:44:21.550 align:middle line:10%
So then expectation is
really highly important,

00:44:21.550 --> 00:44:25.900 align:middle line:10%
because when you start
administering some type

00:44:25.900 --> 00:44:29.875 align:middle line:10%
of placebo, what a person does
is they say-- someone says hey,

00:44:29.875 --> 00:44:32.080 align:middle line:10%
this saline injection is
a-- they don't say saline,

00:44:32.080 --> 00:44:37.480 align:middle line:10%
they say this new drug is going
to take away your Parkinson's.

00:44:37.480 --> 00:44:39.820 align:middle line:90%
And the doctor's enthusiastic.

00:44:39.820 --> 00:44:44.830 align:middle line:84%
And the patient begins to select
the potential in the quantum

00:44:44.830 --> 00:44:49.640 align:middle line:84%
field, a new reality, a
new idea, a new future,

00:44:49.640 --> 00:44:52.460 align:middle line:84%
and then they begin
to emotionally embrace

00:44:52.460 --> 00:44:55.270 align:middle line:84%
what it would feel
like to be well.

00:44:55.270 --> 00:44:58.290 align:middle line:84%
They begin to create
an elevated emotion.

00:44:58.290 --> 00:45:00.080 align:middle line:84%
So when you combine
a clear intention

00:45:00.080 --> 00:45:02.500 align:middle line:84%
with an elevated emotion,
the way you think

00:45:02.500 --> 00:45:05.030 align:middle line:84%
and the way you feel creates
a new state of being.

00:45:05.030 --> 00:45:07.190 align:middle line:84%
And it is those
chemicals that begin

00:45:07.190 --> 00:45:10.970 align:middle line:84%
to change the body
by thought alone.

00:45:10.970 --> 00:45:13.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you create it in the
quantum field and bring it in?

00:45:13.900 --> 00:45:15.250 align:middle line:90%
Or do you go to it?

00:45:15.250 --> 00:45:16.660 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Doesn't matter.

00:45:16.660 --> 00:45:19.000 align:middle line:84%
It really is-- the
patient has no idea.

00:45:19.000 --> 00:45:20.660 align:middle line:84%
You can tell a
patient hey, look,

00:45:20.660 --> 00:45:23.550 align:middle line:84%
we're going to do this
serious surgery on your knee.

00:45:23.550 --> 00:45:27.250 align:middle line:84%
You can wheel them in there and
you can slice their knee open

00:45:27.250 --> 00:45:29.300 align:middle line:90%
and never do the surgery.

00:45:29.300 --> 00:45:31.680 align:middle line:84%
And this has happened more
than once, it's Mosley's work.

00:45:31.680 --> 00:45:35.670 align:middle line:84%
And it shows, then, that in
two years, six years later,

00:45:35.670 --> 00:45:37.710 align:middle line:84%
these men are running
around with no knee pain,

00:45:37.710 --> 00:45:38.585 align:middle line:90%
full range of motion.

00:45:38.585 --> 00:45:40.300 align:middle line:84%
Well, how the heck
did that happen?

00:45:40.300 --> 00:45:42.880 align:middle line:84%
Well, they selected,
they believed, accepted,

00:45:42.880 --> 00:45:45.980 align:middle line:84%
and surrendered to the idea
that the surgery would work.

00:45:45.980 --> 00:45:50.310 align:middle line:84%
And the thought began to imprint
into the autonomic nervous

00:45:50.310 --> 00:45:52.390 align:middle line:84%
system, and it was the
autonomic nervous system

00:45:52.390 --> 00:45:53.506 align:middle line:90%
that healed the cartilage.

00:45:53.506 --> 00:45:55.380 align:middle line:84%
They couldn't consciously
heal the cartilage.

00:45:55.380 --> 00:45:55.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:45:55.650 --> 00:45:58.290 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: But they selected
the idea that they were better,

00:45:58.290 --> 00:45:59.650 align:middle line:84%
they emotionally
embraced it, and then

00:45:59.650 --> 00:46:01.233 align:middle line:84%
they surrendered it
to a greater mind.

00:46:01.233 --> 00:46:04.432 align:middle line:84%
And it's exactly the formula for
how the second mechanism works.

00:46:04.432 --> 00:46:06.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You've said the word
surrender several times.

00:46:06.640 --> 00:46:07.890 align:middle line:90%
Now, what do you mean by that?

00:46:07.890 --> 00:46:10.370 align:middle line:84%
You give up all of the
ideas of it not working?

00:46:10.370 --> 00:46:11.620 align:middle line:90%
What do you mean by surrender?

00:46:11.620 --> 00:46:14.078 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: If I said to you,
hey, I know you're stressing,

00:46:14.078 --> 00:46:16.855 align:middle line:84%
but you're leaving town and
I'm going to clean your house.

00:46:16.855 --> 00:46:18.980 align:middle line:84%
If you know I'm going to
come and clean your house,

00:46:18.980 --> 00:46:21.210 align:middle line:84%
you're going to
surrender like, OK.

00:46:21.210 --> 00:46:22.456 align:middle line:90%
I'm letting go.

00:46:22.456 --> 00:46:24.080 align:middle line:84%
So when you let go,
it means you're not

00:46:24.080 --> 00:46:25.640 align:middle line:84%
going to analyze how
it's going to happen

00:46:25.640 --> 00:46:26.720 align:middle line:90%
or when it's going to happen.

00:46:26.720 --> 00:46:28.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you have no
expectations of the outcome.

00:46:28.190 --> 00:46:29.231 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: That's right.

00:46:29.231 --> 00:46:31.630 align:middle line:84%
You're not trying to
control the outcome.

00:46:31.630 --> 00:46:33.820 align:middle line:84%
So people who surrender
really well tend

00:46:33.820 --> 00:46:37.959 align:middle line:84%
to be the people who just have
the most trust in the future.

00:46:37.959 --> 00:46:40.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's a key right
there is surrendering.

00:46:40.000 --> 00:46:43.660 align:middle line:84%
It's a big part of it, because
you can create the imagery

00:46:43.660 --> 00:46:45.370 align:middle line:90%
and intensify the emotion.

00:46:45.370 --> 00:46:47.130 align:middle line:84%
I think the surrendering
has a huge part

00:46:47.130 --> 00:46:49.180 align:middle line:84%
to do with it, because
you let go of the control.

00:46:49.180 --> 00:46:49.590 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Yeah.

00:46:49.590 --> 00:46:51.206 align:middle line:84%
And you have to
get out of the way.

00:46:51.206 --> 00:46:52.830 align:middle line:84%
And we've seen hundreds
of brain scans,

00:46:52.830 --> 00:46:55.400 align:middle line:84%
and we know that you and I are
at our best when we get out

00:46:55.400 --> 00:46:55.900 align:middle line:90%
of the way.

00:46:55.900 --> 00:46:57.520 align:middle line:84%
So the second point
is expectation.

00:46:57.520 --> 00:46:58.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And the third--

00:46:58.300 --> 00:46:59.758 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And
we've taught people

00:46:59.758 --> 00:47:01.269 align:middle line:90%
how to do that exact thing.

00:47:01.269 --> 00:47:03.310 align:middle line:84%
Number one, if we're going
back to the first one,

00:47:03.310 --> 00:47:04.726 align:middle line:84%
we've taught them
how to condition

00:47:04.726 --> 00:47:05.880 align:middle line:90%
their body to a new mind.

00:47:05.880 --> 00:47:07.250 align:middle line:90%
We do that in our workshops.

00:47:07.250 --> 00:47:09.700 align:middle line:84%
In the second
scenario, we have them

00:47:09.700 --> 00:47:11.960 align:middle line:84%
select the potential
in the quantum field,

00:47:11.960 --> 00:47:15.190 align:middle line:84%
emotionally embrace it, begin
to teach their body emotionally

00:47:15.190 --> 00:47:17.620 align:middle line:84%
what it's going to feel
like ahead of the event.

00:47:17.620 --> 00:47:20.200 align:middle line:84%
And then we allow them to
surrender to a greater mind

00:47:20.200 --> 00:47:22.780 align:middle line:84%
and to live as if their
prayer's already answered.

00:47:22.780 --> 00:47:24.630 align:middle line:84%
And it's that exact
mechanism that

00:47:24.630 --> 00:47:27.280 align:middle line:84%
begins to start the
healing process.

00:47:27.280 --> 00:47:30.050 align:middle line:10%
But the third thing is
called assigning meaning.

00:47:30.050 --> 00:47:32.150 align:middle line:10%
And when you assign
meaning to something,

00:47:32.150 --> 00:47:33.810 align:middle line:10%
you increase your intention.

00:47:33.810 --> 00:47:35.130 align:middle line:10%
Here is a great experiment.

00:47:35.130 --> 00:47:36.880 align:middle line:84%
They took a group of
Latin American maids

00:47:36.880 --> 00:47:39.960 align:middle line:84%
that worked in a hotel, and
they followed them around in one

00:47:39.960 --> 00:47:40.460 align:middle line:90%
day.

00:47:40.460 --> 00:47:43.590 align:middle line:84%
And they saw them flipping
mattresses, and moving

00:47:43.590 --> 00:47:47.200 align:middle line:84%
furniture, and scrubbing
the walls of the bathroom,

00:47:47.200 --> 00:47:49.670 align:middle line:84%
and making beds,
and pushing carts.

00:47:49.670 --> 00:47:54.560 align:middle line:84%
And the scientists realized
that these women were actually

