00:57:15.742 --> 00:57:17.950 align:middle line:84%
they're not analyzing and
they're not thinking, which

00:57:17.950 --> 00:57:20.770 align:middle line:84%
means their brainwave
patterns naturally

00:57:20.770 --> 00:57:23.780 align:middle line:84%
change from beta to alpha,
and some into theta.

00:57:23.780 --> 00:57:27.340 align:middle line:84%
Not only just change into those
states, but coherent brain wave

00:57:27.340 --> 00:57:27.840 align:middle line:90%
patterns.

00:57:27.840 --> 00:57:31.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's when we start to see
the most significant changes

00:57:31.720 --> 00:57:33.580 align:middle line:90%
that we have measured.

00:57:33.580 --> 00:57:36.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can you help
me with something?

00:57:36.430 --> 00:57:39.350 align:middle line:90%
I think you can.

00:57:39.350 --> 00:57:40.770 align:middle line:84%
Just to make it
practical, I want

00:57:40.770 --> 00:57:44.740 align:middle line:84%
to use a personal example of
something that I'm experiencing

00:57:44.740 --> 00:57:47.210 align:middle line:84%
and how to maybe help
me get out of it.

00:57:47.210 --> 00:57:50.950 align:middle line:84%
So I miss a lot of
opportunities with my daughter.

00:57:50.950 --> 00:57:54.390 align:middle line:84%
She has firsts, or
she has experiences

00:57:54.390 --> 00:57:57.440 align:middle line:84%
that I can't be at because I
can't be there all the time.

00:57:57.440 --> 00:57:59.000 align:middle line:90%
Because I'm a working mom.

00:57:59.000 --> 00:58:02.450 align:middle line:84%
And that's my choice
to do what I do.

00:58:02.450 --> 00:58:04.170 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes it doesn't
work out so well

00:58:04.170 --> 00:58:07.940 align:middle line:84%
because I miss really cool
key events, and it hurts.

00:58:07.940 --> 00:58:09.000 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: I understand.

00:58:09.000 --> 00:58:12.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We went to the
Olympics in 2012 in London,

00:58:12.550 --> 00:58:15.100 align:middle line:90%
and she's a soccer player.

00:58:15.100 --> 00:58:16.564 align:middle line:90%
And I had to leave.

00:58:16.564 --> 00:58:18.730 align:middle line:84%
And my husband and I left
my husband and my daughter

00:58:18.730 --> 00:58:21.020 align:middle line:84%
there, because
they really wanted

00:58:21.020 --> 00:58:24.160 align:middle line:84%
to go to the US versus
Japan soccer game.

00:58:24.160 --> 00:58:26.450 align:middle line:90%
Really wanted to see Hope Solo.

00:58:26.450 --> 00:58:28.850 align:middle line:84%
And it wound up that
they won the game

00:58:28.850 --> 00:58:32.700 align:middle line:84%
and that moment was like burned
in her memory, that has then

00:58:32.700 --> 00:58:37.120 align:middle line:84%
propelled her on to
become a rock star goalie.

00:58:37.120 --> 00:58:40.040 align:middle line:84%
And she had-- and
I wasn't there.

00:58:40.040 --> 00:58:43.290 align:middle line:84%
And I have this enormous
amount of guilt for that.

00:58:43.290 --> 00:58:45.550 align:middle line:84%
And I don't want to
register that into her,

00:58:45.550 --> 00:58:48.160 align:middle line:84%
because it registers
to me all time.

00:58:48.160 --> 00:58:51.930 align:middle line:84%
So how do I get over that
moment of not being there

00:58:51.930 --> 00:58:53.480 align:middle line:84%
during the moment
that propels her

00:58:53.480 --> 00:58:56.140 align:middle line:84%
every time in a
game to do so well?

00:58:56.140 --> 00:58:58.090 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
first of all, guilt

00:58:58.090 --> 00:59:00.309 align:middle line:84%
doesn't serve you
or serve her well.

00:59:00.309 --> 00:59:01.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It doesn't.

00:59:01.100 --> 00:59:02.474 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And
that's a program.

00:59:02.474 --> 00:59:04.130 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I have three
children, and I

00:59:04.130 --> 00:59:08.390 align:middle line:84%
missed certain special days
because I was on the road.

00:59:08.390 --> 00:59:10.470 align:middle line:90%
But I'm just a creative dude.

00:59:10.470 --> 00:59:13.622 align:middle line:84%
So I'm like, OK, let's
film this and we're

00:59:13.622 --> 00:59:14.830 align:middle line:90%
going to watch this together.

00:59:14.830 --> 00:59:16.788 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
celebrate it in the same way

00:59:16.788 --> 00:59:19.900 align:middle line:84%
that you celebrated, or
watch the big game together.

00:59:19.900 --> 00:59:25.830 align:middle line:84%
So the guilt is feeling bad
because you think on some level

00:59:25.830 --> 00:59:27.570 align:middle line:90%
that you're not a good parent.

00:59:27.570 --> 00:59:30.140 align:middle line:84%
See, if you know
you're a good parent,

00:59:30.140 --> 00:59:31.850 align:middle line:90%
then you can't have guilt.

00:59:31.850 --> 00:59:36.150 align:middle line:84%
Because you're clear
that what you're doing

00:59:36.150 --> 00:59:38.200 align:middle line:84%
is making a difference
in the world.

00:59:38.200 --> 00:59:40.240 align:middle line:84%
And you're clear
that you're providing

00:59:40.240 --> 00:59:44.650 align:middle line:84%
a certain amount of revenue
for your family, an income.

00:59:44.650 --> 00:59:48.240 align:middle line:84%
So you're looking at it
through the lens of guilt.

00:59:48.240 --> 00:59:50.700 align:middle line:84%
So I don't have guilt
around it any longer,

00:59:50.700 --> 00:59:52.680 align:middle line:84%
because I don't want
to feel that way.

00:59:52.680 --> 00:59:56.130 align:middle line:84%
What I have is like, OK, I
have to get creative now.

00:59:56.130 --> 01:00:00.812 align:middle line:84%
And if I'm missing an event,
then let's videotape it

01:00:00.812 --> 01:00:02.770 align:middle line:84%
and let's plan on getting
together and watching

01:00:02.770 --> 01:00:04.015 align:middle line:90%
it and celebrating it together.

01:00:04.015 --> 01:00:04.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a good idea.

01:00:04.950 --> 01:00:06.408 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Let's
watch the-- let's

01:00:06.408 --> 01:00:09.620 align:middle line:84%
get the copy of the soccer game
and let's relive it together.

01:00:09.620 --> 01:00:10.925 align:middle line:90%
And let's make it a fun thing.

01:00:10.925 --> 01:00:13.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: >>DISPENZA: She actually
came up with a great solution.

01:00:13.550 --> 01:00:16.740 align:middle line:84%
She says, mom, you're going
to be with me there in spirit.

01:00:16.740 --> 01:00:18.140 align:middle line:90%
And she said that back to me.

01:00:18.140 --> 01:00:18.860 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Or you know what?

01:00:18.860 --> 01:00:21.240 align:middle line:84%
The best thing is have her
recount the whole thing

01:00:21.240 --> 01:00:23.700 align:middle line:84%
and celebrate it with her
while she's telling the story.

01:00:23.700 --> 01:00:25.900 align:middle line:90%
Oh my god, that's incredible.

01:00:25.900 --> 01:00:29.540 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the fact that you're
guilty, or feel guilty, means

01:00:29.540 --> 01:00:33.310 align:middle line:84%
then you're not participating
in the event authentically.

01:00:33.310 --> 01:00:34.900 align:middle line:84%
If there's no
guilt-- I mean, look,

01:00:34.900 --> 01:00:36.200 align:middle line:90%
I've got an Italian mother.

01:00:36.200 --> 01:00:38.470 align:middle line:84%
My mother can't make
me guilty any longer.

01:00:38.470 --> 01:00:40.055 align:middle line:84%
I just don't feel
guilt around her.

01:00:40.055 --> 01:00:40.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

01:00:40.680 --> 01:00:42.180 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: I just,
I don't have it.

01:00:42.180 --> 01:00:43.460 align:middle line:90%
And I love her.

01:00:43.460 --> 01:00:44.025 align:middle line:90%
And so--

01:00:44.025 --> 01:00:45.650 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How did you
get rid of guilt?

01:00:45.650 --> 01:00:48.370 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, sitting
in meditation for many hours

01:00:48.370 --> 01:00:51.040 align:middle line:84%
and becoming aware what guilt
feels like and realizing

01:00:51.040 --> 01:00:52.670 align:middle line:90%
that's not healthy to me--

01:00:52.670 --> 01:00:53.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

01:00:53.170 --> 01:00:55.378 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --and that's
not the kind of relationship

01:00:55.378 --> 01:00:56.470 align:middle line:90%
I want with my mother.

01:00:56.470 --> 01:00:58.900 align:middle line:10%
So now I see my mother, I
kiss her all over the face,

01:00:58.900 --> 01:01:00.330 align:middle line:10%
I hug her, I play with her.

01:01:00.330 --> 01:01:03.020 align:middle line:10%
There is no time for
guilt with me with her

01:01:03.020 --> 01:01:05.780 align:middle line:10%
and that's the relationship
I want to have.

01:01:05.780 --> 01:01:08.330 align:middle line:84%
So you bring your
best to your daughter.

01:01:08.330 --> 01:01:09.580 align:middle line:90%
What's your best?

01:01:09.580 --> 01:01:13.926 align:middle line:84%
Your best is a genuine sense
of celebration of life.

01:01:13.926 --> 01:01:15.550 align:middle line:84%
That's what you bring
to your daughter.

01:01:15.550 --> 01:01:16.816 align:middle line:90%
And enthusiasm.

01:01:16.816 --> 01:01:18.690 align:middle line:84%
And if you say, gosh,
I'm going to miss this.

01:01:18.690 --> 01:01:21.070 align:middle line:10%
I really want to be there,
but let's think together

01:01:21.070 --> 01:01:23.650 align:middle line:10%
how we can do it--
relive it again.

01:01:23.650 --> 01:01:30.450 align:middle line:10%
And so if you decide that
that feeling isn't going away

01:01:30.450 --> 01:01:33.330 align:middle line:10%
and it means more to you
than what you're doing,

01:01:33.330 --> 01:01:36.750 align:middle line:10%
then you have to make a
choice to leave this and be

01:01:36.750 --> 01:01:41.250 align:middle line:10%
present at those events because
it has more value to you.

01:01:41.250 --> 01:01:44.540 align:middle line:84%
But if your value is clear
that you're making a difference

01:01:44.540 --> 01:01:48.010 align:middle line:84%
and this is your life, then
you just have to get creative.

01:01:48.010 --> 01:01:50.770 align:middle line:84%
And a guilty person will
never see creative options.

01:01:50.770 --> 01:01:51.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

01:01:51.270 --> 01:01:51.370 align:middle line:90%
Right.

01:01:51.370 --> 01:01:52.380 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: All they're
doing is waiting

01:01:52.380 --> 01:01:54.560 align:middle line:84%
for the feeling of oh
my god, I blew it again.

01:01:54.560 --> 01:01:55.060 align:middle line:90%
I'm bad.

01:01:55.060 --> 01:01:55.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:01:55.970 --> 01:01:57.678 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: You just
got to get creative.

01:01:57.678 --> 01:02:02.240 align:middle line:84%
So emotions are the end
product of experience.

01:02:02.240 --> 01:02:05.320 align:middle line:84%
The emotion of guilt is
connected in some level

01:02:05.320 --> 01:02:06.630 align:middle line:90%
to your past.

01:02:06.630 --> 01:02:09.170 align:middle line:84%
And you on some level
feel bad because you

01:02:09.170 --> 01:02:10.410 align:middle line:90%
did something wrong.

01:02:10.410 --> 01:02:12.730 align:middle line:84%
And now you feel like
you've done something wrong,

01:02:12.730 --> 01:02:15.390 align:middle line:84%
until you get the clear that
there's nothing wrong with what

01:02:15.390 --> 01:02:17.390 align:middle line:84%
you're doing and
that you are actually

01:02:17.390 --> 01:02:20.622 align:middle line:84%
making a huge difference
in so many people's lives

01:02:20.622 --> 01:02:21.830 align:middle line:90%
and contributing in some way.

01:02:21.830 --> 01:02:23.205 align:middle line:84%
And your daughter's
one day going

01:02:23.205 --> 01:02:26.550 align:middle line:84%
to watch these videos when
you're long gone and love you.

01:02:26.550 --> 01:02:28.820 align:middle line:84%
And your grandkids are
going to watch these videos

01:02:28.820 --> 01:02:31.770 align:middle line:84%
and they're going to say,
wow, that woman was amazing.

01:02:31.770 --> 01:02:32.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You're right.

01:02:32.670 --> 01:02:34.470 align:middle line:90%
Guilt does rob time.

01:02:34.470 --> 01:02:35.020 align:middle line:90%
It does.

01:02:35.020 --> 01:02:35.700 align:middle line:90%
It takes away time--

01:02:35.700 --> 01:02:36.090 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: And energy.

01:02:36.090 --> 01:02:37.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --from us and together.

01:02:37.600 --> 01:02:39.130 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, absolutely.

01:02:39.130 --> 01:02:41.270 align:middle line:90%
Well, thank you so much.

01:02:41.270 --> 01:02:45.350 align:middle line:84%
Once again, I can now
take that knowledge

01:02:45.350 --> 01:02:48.340 align:middle line:84%
and move that into
experience and then

01:02:48.340 --> 01:02:50.297 align:middle line:90%
move it into a pattern.

01:02:50.297 --> 01:02:51.880 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Just
create something new.

01:02:51.880 --> 01:02:52.379 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yep.

01:02:52.379 --> 01:02:53.640 align:middle line:90%
That's exactly what I'll do.

01:02:53.640 --> 01:02:56.610 align:middle line:84%
I'll take the thinking
to the doing to the being

01:02:56.610 --> 01:02:59.300 align:middle line:90%
and create a new experience.

01:02:59.300 --> 01:03:02.140 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And plus, your
daughter has mirror neurons

01:03:02.140 --> 01:03:05.127 align:middle line:84%
and you don't want her
to watch you in guilt.

01:03:05.127 --> 01:03:05.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:03:05.710 --> 01:03:07.260 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Because then
she will imprint that--

01:03:07.260 --> 01:03:07.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There goes the pattern.

01:03:07.990 --> 01:03:09.990 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --and you will
pass that on to her daughter

01:03:09.990 --> 01:03:10.823 align:middle line:90%
and to her daughter.

01:03:10.823 --> 01:03:12.617 align:middle line:90%
You have to be the ideal.

01:03:12.617 --> 01:03:13.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a bigger picture.

01:03:13.950 --> 01:03:14.360 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:03:14.360 --> 01:03:15.780 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Now,
that's the greatest

01:03:15.780 --> 01:03:16.850 align:middle line:84%
thing you can do
for your daughter.

01:03:16.850 --> 01:03:16.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, that's true.

01:03:16.930 --> 01:03:18.700 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Greater than
showing up at those events.

01:03:18.700 --> 01:03:20.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It could affect
future generations.

01:03:20.590 --> 01:03:22.215 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Free
yourself and free her.

01:03:22.215 --> 01:03:22.964 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Thank you.

01:03:22.964 --> 01:03:23.906 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

